🎟️ FlashTix Live
⚡ Real-Time Ticketing Platform with API Gateway & Rate Limiting

FlashTix is a high-performance, distributed ticketing system designed for handling extreme flash-sale traffic without downtime, data loss, or API overload.

It combines:

🧠 Event-driven architecture
🚪 API Gateway with rate limiting
⚡ Real-time updates
🔄 Asynchronous processing
🏗️ System Architecture

<p align="center"> <img src="./asserts/System-Architecture.png" width="850"/> <br/> <em>FlashTix Distributed Architecture with Gateway, Kafka, Redis, RabbitMQ, and MinIO</em> </p>
🚪 API Gateway (NEW 🔥)

FlashTix uses a dedicated API Gateway layer built with:

Spring Cloud Gateway
Redis (for rate limiting)
⚡ Why Gateway?
Centralized routing
Security enforcement
Rate limiting (prevents system crash during flash sales)
Load control before hitting backend services
🛡️ Rate Limiting Strategy

Your gateway implements IP-based rate limiting:

@Bean
public KeyResolver ipKeyResolver() {
return exchange -> Mono.just(
exchange.getRequest().getRemoteAddress().getAddress().getHostAddress()
);
}

📌 Meaning:

Each user (IP) gets limited requests/sec
Prevents bots & traffic spikes
Protects Kafka + DB from overload

